em> <em>butyricum</em> butyric acid; N.L. masc. n. <em>coccus</em> a coccus; N.L. masc. n. <em>Butyricicoccus</em> coccoid-shaped bacterium that produces butyrate).</s></p><p class="description"><s>Cells are Gram-positive, anaerobic, non-motile, coccoid and usually arranged in pairs (occasionally in short chains).</s><s>Produce butyrate, H<sub>2</sub> and CO<sub>2</sub> and utilize acetate in M2GSC broth.</s><s>The phylogenetic position is in a novel lineage in the class <em>Clostridia</em> of the phylum <em>Firmicutes</em>.</s><s>The type species is <em>Butyricicoccus pullicaecorum</em>.</s></p></content></protolog>